 the British take themselves too seriously\",<ref name=\"Punch\" /> a quotation that Ward Lock used on the rear covers of many of Yates's later volumes.\n\n==References==\n\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Bibliography==\n* {{Cite book|ref=harv|title=Dornford Yates |last= Smithers |first=AJ |publisher=[[Hodder & Stoughton|Hodder and Stoughton]] |year=1982 |location=London |isbn=0 340 27547 2}}\n\n[[Category:1920 short story collections]]\n[[Category:Ward Lock & Co books]]\n[[Category:Short story collections by Dornford Yates]]\n", "name_user": "RGCorris", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBackground:add comma", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Courts_of_Idleness"}
